The Policemen, who shot and killed a tailor in Oshodi, Lagos while making an illegal arrest, have been apprehended by a Police Task Force team. The arrested policemen are: Orubu Olusola, Apalowo Ola and Kasai Sule who are all Inspectors. Others are two Sergeants â€“ Momoh Ogwuche and Adoga Collins. They are all attached to the Akinpelu Division in Oshodi, and according to the Task Force, they will be charged for murder.